node.text:
Last week I posted F-Factor Spicy, Cheesy No-Carb Pasta 🍝 .  Today, I will teach you how to journal it.
 
I have found that my clients who regularly journal have the greatest success on F-Factor ✨ .  Journaling allows you to see patterns of behavior (are you skipping breakfast? are you snacking at night?) while making you aware of habits that may be undermining your success.
 
But most of all, journaling will help you to learn which foods are a good source of fiber and show you if you are getting enough.  F-Factor’s philosophy encourages you eat at least 35g of fiber/day and a designated number of net carbs on each phase (Step 1, Step 2 and Maintenance). Fiber is essential for keeping you full ✅ , revving up your metabolism ✅ and offers numerous health benefits ✅ .  Net carbs are used for energy and only in the absence of net carbs does your body burn fat for fuel.  Being aware of how much net carb you have ingested is crucial to helping you achieve your  weight management goals.
 
New to F-Factor? F-Factor offers a F-Factor Journal 📗 complete with shopping lists and sample meals.  Do you prefer to journal on your smartphone 📱? F-Factor has an app (download it for FREE from the App Store).
 
Do you journal on F-Factor? Drop a 💚 if you do!

node.text:
Almost a year later, I am finally finding the courage to use my voice to tell my truth. 

The past year was difficult for many people. It certainly was the worst year of my life. I saw my 20 year company and my professional reputation destroyed by a targeted smear campaign. 

I was harassed and cyberstalked by Emily Gellis. She spent months disparaging me, my program, my products, my employees and family members.  She was relentless and cruel. And the world watched and the media joined the feeding frenzy of cancel culture. 

I had faith that the truth would prevail. I believe it finally has. 

Thank you for those who have never wavered in their support. Thank you to my loyal clients and customers for never doubting. Thank you to my team at F-Factor for bravely holding your heads up high during this challenging time. Thank you to my friends and family for helping me get through this. And thank you for the love of the F-Factor Community. Combined, you all provided me with the strength to use my voice, to tell my truth, and move forward with dignity. 💚
#ffactor #ffactorapproved #ffactorforlife

node.text:
Fiber and Protein at Every Meal Makes Losing No Big Deal 💁🏻‍♀️

Fiber source: high fiber cereals, 1/3c Bran Buds 13g fiber, 1/4c Catalina Crunch 5g
1/2 cup mixed berries 3g, 1 Tbl @sukrinusa fiber gold syrup 10g fiber 💚 

Protein: choose from 3/4 cGreek yogurt 18g, 1/2c Cottage Cheese 11g or 1/2x Ricotta Cheese 16g protein ✨

You can also sprinkle on some @zenbasil for added fiber, calcium, potassium and iron 👏🏼

Benefits of this Step 1 Breakfast:
Fiber revs up metabolism ✅ , keeps you full for hours ✅ , lowers cholesterol ✅ , alleviates constipation ✅ and creates a healthy gut ✅

Protein: keeps you full and is necessary for building muscle which is why it’s ideal to eat a high protein breakfast post workout 💪🏼

What’s your favorite #ffactor #Step1 Breakfast? Share with me below 👇🏼 #ffactor 💚

node.text: It’s been a while since I have felt this happy and connected to my work. So what changed today? Today I saw more clients than usual. Sure, counseling clients is intellectually stimulating- I am able to share my passion for nutrition science and educate my clients with sound information.  But it goes beyond that— what truly fills me up is connecting with my clients on a personal note. Being with my clients presents the opportunity for me to  put my heart into them and allow me to express how much I care about them. The joy of helping people to live their best life is one of the main reasons I chose to be an RD. Nothing makes me smile more than putting a smile on someone else’s face. Thank you to the clients I saw today- I owe this smile to you. 💚 #ffactorlife #factorapproved

node.text:
Hands down, one of the most popular F-Factor recipes is the F-Factor waffle 🧇 . It’s light, fluffy, satisfying, and delicious. People’s minds were blown when they learned that they also could help you to lose weight and improve your health! Now that F-Factor launched a vegan 20/20 FIBER/PROTEIN Powder 🌱 , we created two new recipes: a dairy-free version and vegan.  
 
Like the Original F-Factor Waffle 🧇 , they have at least 20g fiber, and 20g protein and are low in net carbs. Fiber revs metabolism, keeps you feeling full, and promotes a healthy gut.  While protein is an essential nutrient for building muscle 💪🏻 . And because the waffles are also low in carbs, your body can burn fat for fuel (hello flat tummy)!
 
All 3 variety of waffles are:
-Gluten-free ✅
-High fiber ✅
-High protein ✅
-No Sugar Added ✅
-Soy Free ✅

All 3 recipes can be found on ffactor.com (link in bio).  Thanks to F-Factor, waffles and weight loss can go hand-in-hand (or rather, hand-to-mouth) 😊.  Drop a 💚 if you’ve tried F-Factor waffles! #RecipeRehab #FFACTORAPPROVED

node.title: The Healthiest Weight Loss Waffles in the World! 💚🧇

node.text:
When it comes to Vodka Sauce dishes, Carbone’s is KING 👑—their Spicy Vodka  Rigatoni is irresistible, and hands down, it’s one of the best pasta dishes I’ve ever had 🍝.  Because reservations at Carbone are hard to come by, I set out to create my own version so I could enjoy this dish from home whenever I wanted.  After a few tries, I  pulled it off!  F-Factor’s version of Carbone’s Spicy Rigatoni tastes as delicious as the original dish, but my version contains fiber ✅ and protein ✅ , no cream (yes, my version is VEGAN), and is lower in net carbs ✅ despite using real pasta. The result? A pasta dish good that is equally GOOD for your health and your waistline! I can’t wait for you to make it! 💚

Comment below 👇🏼 if you’ve had the Spicy Rigatoni Vodka at Carbone’s, and you are excited to try this recipe! 🍽

node.text:
Last week I posted F-Factor Spicy, Cheesy No-Carb Pasta 🍝 .  Today, I will teach you how to journal it.
 
I have found that my clients who regularly journal have the greatest success on F-Factor ✨ .  Journaling allows you to see patterns of behavior (are you skipping breakfast? are you snacking at night?) while making you aware of habits that may be undermining your success.
 
But most of all, journaling will help you to learn which foods are a good source of fiber and show you if you are getting enough.  F-Factor’s philosophy encourages you eat at least 35g of fiber/day and a designated number of net carbs on each phase (Step 1, Step 2 and Maintenance). Fiber is essential for keeping you full ✅ , revving up your metabolism ✅ and offers numerous health benefits ✅ .  Net carbs are used for energy and only in the absence of net carbs does your body burn fat for fuel.  Being aware of how much net carb you have ingested is crucial to helping you achieve your  weight management goals.
 
New to F-Factor? F-Factor offers a F-Factor Journal 📗 complete with shopping lists and sample meals.  Do you prefer to journal on your smartphone 📱? F-Factor has an app (download it for FREE from the App Store).
 
Do you journal on F-Factor? Drop a 💚 if you do!

node.text:
“You may have the universe if I may have Italy.” - Giuseppe Verdi

The food🍝. The wine🍷. The warmth of the people. The style. The history. The beauty of the countryside. The color of the sea. Italy🇮🇹 forever has my heart. Other than where you currently live, where else could you see living one day? Share with me below. 👇🏼#ffactortravels #italianlifestyle

node.accessibility_caption: Gelato, Italy, summer, summer nights, Amal du coast, ice cream, fashion, summer in italy, rome

node.text:
📞 Calling all ice cream lovers!  When you’re in Rome be sure to visit Giolitti- what many consider the best gelato in Rome 🇮🇹. They offer over 50 flavors, including vegan options- it’s so hard to choose just 2 flavors when ordering a cone🍦. 

So what is the difference between gelato and ice cream?

✨  Ingredients:
While both gelato and ice cream contain cream, milk, and sugar. Authentic gelato uses more milk and less cream and generally doesn’t contain egg yolks.

✨ Texture: 
Gelato contains less air than American ice cream, resulting in a denser and creamier texture. 

✨ Flavor: 
Because it contains less butterfat to coat your palate, it allows the flavors to emerge more (if you have ever tasted mango gelato- you’ve experienced this  —  it tastes just identical to the fruit).

✨ Temperature: 
Italian gelato is served about 10 to 15 degrees warmer than American ice cream, at about 7 to 12 degrees Fahrenheit, so your mouth is less numb and better able to taste it.

✨ Serving Style:
Authentic Italian gelato isn’t scooped, it’s served with a spade. Dig it?

My favorites gelatos are usually fruit flavors like Blackberry, Pear , Fig, Banana 🍌 , Pineapple 🍍 , Mango 🥭, or Melon 🍈. But I also love a scoop of dark chocolate 🍫 and coffee ☕️.  If you had to choose 2 flavors of gelato, what would it be? (Need flavor inspo? Check out my stories where I show the case of all the flavors) 💚 #ffactortravels #ffactorlife

The result.. satisfying Italian meals that fill you up, not out.
